  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Observational study aimed to test the ability of Neutrophil Gelatinase-associated Lipocalin
      (NGAL) concentration in blood and urine to predict and diagnose early acute renal failure
      (ARF) in patients after cardiac surgery with/without Cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
